==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wheatstones rods
<hw>Wheat"stone's rods</hw>. <fld>(Acoustics)</fld> <def>Flexible rods
the period of vibration of which in two planes at right angles are in
some exact ratio to one another. When one end of such a rod is fixed,
the free end describes in vibrating the corresponding Lissajous figure.
So called because devised by Sir Charles Wheatstone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wheatworm</ent>⟦br⟧
